# The Dockerfile bakes orchestrator/, scripts/, prompts/, and .claude-plugin/
# into the image so Fly.io Machines can run without a bind mount (§0.5).
# Exclude everything else to keep the build context lean — .git, tests,
# caches, and docs are not needed inside the image and traversing them over
# the host-to-VM bridge (on Colima/macOS) wastes time.
#
# We negate Dockerfile + .dockerignore so legacy builders (older `docker
# build` / some podman modes) that honor `*` literally still find them.
# Modern BuildKit always reads the Dockerfile regardless, so the negations
# are belt-and-suspenders for cross-tool compatibility.
*
!Dockerfile
!.dockerignore
!orchestrator/
!scripts/
!prompts/
!.claude-plugin/
